Both deliverables are in place.

**`transcript.json`** — 25 iterations, 85 hypotheses, 85 analyses, schema-validated. Top-level fields populated (`dataset_id=ds001_aml`, `model_id=claude-opus-4-7`, `harness_id=claude-code@named-aml-analysis`, `max_iterations=25`).

**`analysis_summary.txt`** — narrative synthesis of what the actual data showed:
- ECOG, albumin, CRP, weight loss, blast %, WBC are the dominant predictors of objective response.
- Venetoclax/azacitidine has a small positive effect (amplified in unfit and NPM1-mutated patients).
- Most biomarker-matched targeted-therapy interactions (FLT3-ITD x midostaurin/gilteritinib; IDH2 x enasidenib) were NOT significant; the IDH1 x ivosidenib interaction was significant but in the opposite direction from textbook expectations.
- TP53 and complex karyotype showed no main effect; complex karyotype interacted negatively with 7+3.
- A residual racial disparity (lower ORR in Black vs. White patients) persisted after multivariable adjustment.
- Solid-tumor markers, non-myeloid genomic alterations, and pharmacogenomic SNPs showed no association (internal-validity sanity check).
